"""
Production-ready attribute generation runner for large CSV inputs.

Design goals:
- Input columns: hs_code, product_description
- Create stable row_id from input order and record_uuid from the input UUID column
- Batch size fixed at 6 by default
- Normal concurrency: 40 workers
- Backpressure concurrency: 12 workers
- SQLite status.db is the scalable resume source of truth; master_status.csv remains audit
- Split outputs: success, low-attribute, model errors, server failures, OOM failures, metrics
- Bounded in-flight scheduler: do not submit whole file at once
- Retry server errors with exponential backoff
- Abort safely on startup server failure, repeated server failures, or OOM

Example:
    python attribute_production_runner.py \
      --input /home/gunashekhar/attributes/Sample_1.csv \
      --output-dir /home/gunashekhar/attributes/run_001
"""

